description:
The Protestant Reformation had swept across Europe in the 16th century, so in this episode we uncover the Scandinavian Reformation. The Reformation strongholds in Germany, Switzerland, England and Scotland, had left a trail of conflict and martyrdom in its wake. However, in the Nordic countries of Scandinavia, the truth took hold in a quieter, inconspicuous manner, leaving behind a powerful legacy.

To find out more information about the Scandinavian Reformation please visit our website.
http://www.lineagejourney.com/reformation/movements/the-scandinavian-reformation/
